@cole-bq I'm interested with your exploration. Using Java's Exception to stop the iteration is not recommended since it has to fill stack trace which hurts the performance. The workaround now is to use Exception without stack trace.

I checked all places which catch the NoSuchElementException, see the below, and none of them care about the stacktrace, just wants to break the loop or traversal, like this patch wants to address.

Now, there are some other graph DB which already refers to Tinkerpop and depends on the exception to do something in their logic, like Janusgraph mentioned in this issue. So, if you prefer to some other solution, please consider the backward compatibility.  

